#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:8
#: 3e1e60288b3f4bb4b3498642046b2ef4
msgid ""
"Telethon is more than just another viable alternative when developing "
"bots for Telegram. If you haven't decided which wrapper library for bots "
"to use yet, using Telethon from the beginning may save you some headaches"
" later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:13
#: c15e032fc03a41a28c703238d16fc9f9
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:16
#: 9e8a47b3f4c64652b1235a312a92f9e5
msgid "What is Bot API?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:18
#: b530e5c7ef0543be8584823464e2b71e
msgid ""
"The `Telegram Bot API`_, also known as HTTP Bot API and from now on "
"referred to as simply \"Bot API\" is Telegram's official way for "
"developers to control their own Telegram bots. Quoting their main page:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:22
#: 8fa4e2e41b554e54a2670647bc5c1f00
msgid ""
"The Bot API is an HTTP-based interface created for developers keen on "
"building bots for Telegram."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:25
#: e3979a65736d4b52af19179073a2c489
msgid ""
"To learn how to create and set up a bot, please consult our `Introduction"
" to Bots`_ and `Bot FAQ`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:28
#: fc4a1d0d073e427b9c18208edd8dc767
msgid ""
"Bot API is simply an HTTP endpoint which translates your requests to it "
"into MTProto calls through tdlib_, their bot backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:31
#: ebd314bc46eb4e8594505beed298727b
msgid ""
"Configuration of your bot, such as its available commands and auto-"
"completion, is configured through `@BotFather <https://t.me/BotFather>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:36
#: 77a2f4bd2e5f475195b491a90180b0c0
msgid "What is MTProto?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:38
#: 0af2bc30b47d417fbcf93e2e20837de4
msgid ""
"MTProto_ is Telegram's own protocol to communicate with their API when "
"you connect to their servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:41
#: aeca32cc34d949e9a80b953a06447d6b
msgid ""
"Telethon is an alternative MTProto-based backend written entirely in "
"Python and much easier to setup and use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:44
#: 3158a17da0904a5899d794d8b80c5f09
msgid ""
"Both official applications and third-party clients (like your own "
"applications) logged in as either user or bots **can use MTProto** to "
"communicate directly with Telegram's API (which is not the HTTP bot API)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:48
#: 2faf213ce51e4f4ca63964072eab7a7f
msgid "When we talk about MTProto, we often mean \"MTProto-based clients\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:52
#: 3fc79c1d50a84e78a513a1abffa20a9b
msgid "Advantages of MTProto over Bot API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:54
#: aac2bbb288bf46b79cf2f2b52fa629a7
msgid ""
"MTProto clients (like Telethon) connect directly to Telegram's servers, "
"which means there is no HTTP connection, no \"polling\" or \"web hooks\"."
" This means **less overhead**, since the protocol used between you and "
"the server is much more compact than HTTP requests with responses in "
"wasteful JSON."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:59
#: 71e56928804441cc8f2016c194e617d1
msgid ""
"Since there is a direct connection to Telegram's servers, even if their "
"Bot API endpoint is down, you can still have connection to Telegram "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:62
#: 3f6eb276cdfd47178515acc5fe939bf5
msgid ""
"Using a MTProto client, you are also not limited to the public API that "
"they expose, and instead, **you have full control** of what your bot can "
"do. Telethon offers you all the power with often **much easier usage** "
"than any of the available Python Bot API wrappers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:67
#: 2c2c799ee2104825b8f830296a0775f8
msgid ""
"If your application ever needs user features because bots cannot do "
"certain things, you will be able to easily login as a user and even keep "
"your bot without having to learn a new library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:71
#: e768fdbd15ca43eba45c4e99c496fc34
msgid ""
"If less overhead and full control didn't convince you to use Telethon "
"yet, check out the wiki page `MTProto vs HTTP Bot API`_ with a more "
"exhaustive and up-to-date list of differences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:77
#: 826e8ad4069b472bbfda68117a141e24
msgid "Migrating from Bot API to Telethon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:79
#: 748873b9d2c5481db8f48ca99e06aa43
msgid ""
"It doesn't matter if you wrote your bot with requests_ and you were "
"making API requests manually, or if you used a wrapper library like "
"python-telegram-bot_ or pyTelegramBotAPI_. It's never too late to migrate"
" to Telethon!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/botapi-vs-mtproto.rst:84
#: 7ccdc66a979b403b91322d925ba9045c
msgid ""
"If you were using an asynchronous library like aiohttp_ or a wrapper like"
" aiogram_ or dumbot_, it will be even easier, because Telethon is also an"
" asynchronous library."
msgstr ""

